  "question": "Digital Signatures",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <title>Digital Signatures — Interactive Demo</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Arial; margin: 20px; color: #111; background: #f7f9fc; }\n    h1 { margin-top: 0; }\n    .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 18px; }\n    .card { background: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(20,20,40,0.06); }\n    textarea { width: 100%; min-height: 100px; font-family: monospace; padding: 8px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid #dce6f2; background: #fbfdff; resize: vertical; }\n    input[type=\"text\"] { width: 100%; padding: 8px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid #dce6f2; background: #fbfdff; }\n    label { font-weight: 600; display:block; margin-bottom:6px; }\n    button { padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 6px; border: none; cursor: pointer; background: #2563eb; color: #fff; }\n    button.secondary { background: #e6eefc; color: #0b3c91; }\n    .row { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:8px; }\n    pre { white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; background:#fbfdff; padding:10px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #e6edf6; }\n    .small { font-size: 13px; color: #444; }\n    .ok { color: #0b6d0b; font-weight:700; }\n    .bad { color:#a00; font-weight:700; }\n    footer { margin-top: 18px; font-size: 13px; color:#555; }\n    .muted { color: #666; font-size: 13px; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Digital Signatures — Interactive Demo</h1>\n  <p class=\"muted\">This page demonstrates how digital signatures work using Web Crypto (ECDSA P-256 + SHA-256). You can generate a key pair, sign a message with the private key (kept in this browser session), and verify the signature with the public key.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"grid\">\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <label>1) Key pair</label>\n      <div class=\"small\">Generate an asymmetric key pair (private key used for signing, public key used to verify).</div>\n      <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <button id=\"generateBtn\">Generate Key Pair</button>\n        <button id=\"exportPubBtn\" class=\"secondary\" disabled>Export Public Key (PEM)</button>\n        <button id=\"exportPrivBtn\" class=\"secondary\" disabled>Export Private Key (PEM)</button>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <label>Public Key (PEM)</label>\n        <textarea id=\"publicPem\" readonly placeholder=\"Public key will appear here...\"></textarea>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n          <button id=\"copyPub\" class=\"secondary\" disabled>Copy</button>\n          <button id=\"importPub\" class=\"secondary\">Import Public Key (paste PEM)</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <label>Private Key (PEM)</label>\n        <textarea id=\"privatePem\" readonly placeholder=\"Private key will appear here if exported...\"></textarea>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n          <button id=\"copyPriv\" class=\"secondary\" disabled>Copy</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <label>2) Message to sign</label>\n      <textarea id=\"message\">The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog</textarea>\n      <div class=\"row\">\n        <button id=\"tamperBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Tamper Message (flip a char)</button>\n        <button id=\"clearTamper\" class=\"secondary\">Reset Message</button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <label>3) Sign</label>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n          <button id=\"signBtn\" disabled>Sign Message</button>\n          <button id=\"signAgain\" class=\"secondary\" disabled>Sign Again (new signature)</button>\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n          <label>Signature (Base64)</label>\n          <textarea id=\"signature\" readonly placeholder=\"Signature will appear here...\"></textarea>\n          <div class=\"row\">\n            <button id=\"copySig\" class=\"secondary\" disabled>Copy Signature</button>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <label>4) Verify</label>\n      <div class=\"small\">Verify the signature using the public key and message. You can import a public key (PEM) or use the one generated above.</div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <label>Public Key to Verify With (PEM)</label>\n        <textarea id=\"verifyPublicPem\" placeholder=\"Paste a PEM public key here (or leave blank to use generated public key)\"></textarea>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <label>Signature (Base64)</label>\n        <input type=\"text\" id=\"verifySignature\" placeholder=\"Paste base64 signature (or leave blank to use generated signature)\" />\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <button id=\"verifyBtn\" class=\"\">Verify</button>\n        <button id=\"verifyTampered\" class=\"secondary\">Verify Tampered (show failure)</button>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <label>Result</label>\n        <pre id=\"result\">No verification yet.</pre>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <label>About this demo</label>\n      <div class=\"small\" style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">\n        How it works (simplified):\n        <ul>\n          <li>Generate ECDSA key pair (P-256). Private key stays in your browser memory unless you export it.</li>\n          <li>To sign: the message is hashed (SHA-256) and the private key creates a signature over that hash.</li>\n          <li>To verify: the verifier uses the signer's public key to check the signature against the message hash. If even one bit of the message or signature changed, verification fails.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"small\">\n        Note: This demo uses the Web Crypto API. Keys and operations happen in your browser; no data is sent anywhere.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <footer>\n    Built with Web Crypto API — ECDSA P-256 + SHA-256. Signature format: DER-encoded (r and s).\n  </footer>\n\n  <script>\n    // Utility helpers\n    const enc = new TextEncoder();\n    const dec = new TextDecoder();\n\n    function bufToBase64(buffer) {\n      const bytes = new Uint8Array(buffer);\n      let binary = '';\n      for (let i = 0; i < bytes.byteLength; i++) {\n        binary += String.fromCharCode(bytes[i]);\n      }\n      return btoa(binary);\n    }\n\n    function base64ToBuf(base64) {\n      const binary = atob(base64);\n      const len = binary.length;\n      const bytes = new Uint8Array(len);\n      for (let i = 0; i < len; i++) {\n        bytes[i] = binary.charCodeAt(i);\n      }\n      return bytes.buffer;\n    }\n\n    function wrapPem(b64, type) {\n      const lines = b64.match(/.{1,64}/g) || [];\n      return `-----BEGIN ${type}-----\\n${lines.join('\\n')}\\n-----END ${type}-----\\n`;\n    }\n\n    function unwrapPem(pem) {\n      return pem.replace(/-----(BEGIN|END)[\\w\\s]+-----/g, '').replace(/\\s+/g, '');\n    }\n\n    // UI elements\n    const generateBtn = document.getElementById('generateBtn');\n    const exportPubBtn = document.getElementById('exportPubBtn');\n    const exportPrivBtn = document.getElementById('exportPrivBtn');\n    const publicPemArea = document.getElementById('publicPem');\n    const privatePemArea = document.getElementById('privatePem');\n    const copyPubBtn = document.getElementById('copyPub');\n    const copyPrivBtn = document.getElementById('copyPriv');\n    const importPubBtn = document.getElementById('importPub');\n\n    const messageArea = document.getElementById('message');\n    const tamperBtn = document.getElementById('tamperBtn');\n    const clearTamper = document.getElementById('clearTamper');\n\n    const signBtn = document.getElementById('signBtn');\n    const signAgain = document.getElementById('signAgain');\n    const signatureArea = document.getElementById('signature');\n    const copySigBtn = document.getElementById('copySig');\n\n    const verifyPublicPem = document.getElementById('verifyPublicPem');\n    const verifySignature = document.getElementById('verifySignature');\n    const verifyBtn = document.getElementById('verifyBtn');\n    const verifyTampered = document.getElementById('verifyTampered');\n    const resultPre = document.getElementById('result');\n\n    // Crypto state\n    let cryptoKeyPair = null; // {publicKey, privateKey}\n    let exportedPublicPem = '';\n    let exportedPrivatePem = '';\n    let lastSignatureB64 = '';\n\n    async function generateKeyPair() {\n      const keyPair = await crypto.subtle.generateKey(\n        {\n          name: 'ECDSA',\n          namedCurve: 'P-256'\n        },\n        true, // extractable so we can export for demo\n        ['sign', 'verify']\n      );\n      cryptoKeyPair = keyPair;\n      // Export public and private keys to PEM for display\n      const spki = await crypto.subtle.exportKey('spki', keyPair.publicKey);\n      const pkcs8 = await crypto.subtle.exportKey('pkcs8', keyPair.privateKey);\n      const pubB64 = bufToBase64(spki);\n      const privB64 = bufToBase64(pkcs8);\n      exportedPublicPem = wrapPem(pubB64, 'PUBLIC KEY');\n      exportedPrivatePem = wrapPem(privB64, 'PRIVATE KEY');\n\n      publicPemArea.value = exportedPublicPem;\n      privatePemArea.value = exportedPrivatePem;\n      exportPubBtn.disabled = false;\n      exportPrivBtn.disabled = false;\n      copyPubBtn.disabled = false;\n      copyPrivBtn.disabled = false;\n      signBtn.disabled = false;\n      signAgain.disabled = true;\n      copySigBtn.disabled = true;\n      resultPre.textContent = 'Key pair generated. Ready to sign.';\n      lastSignatureB64 = '';\n      signatureArea.value = '';\n      verifySignature.value = '';\n    }\n\n    async function signMessage() {\n      if (!cryptoKeyPair || !cryptoKeyPair.privateKey) {\n        alert('No private key available. Generate a key pair first.');\n        return;\n      }\n      const messageStr = messageArea.value;\n      const data = enc.encode(messageStr);\n      try {\n        const sig = await crypto.subtle.sign(\n          { name: 'ECDSA', hash: { name: 'SHA-256' } },\n          cryptoKeyPair.privateKey,\n          data\n        );\n        lastSignatureB64 = bufToBase64(sig);\n        signatureArea.value = lastSignatureB64;\n        verifySignature.value = lastSignatureB64;\n        signAgain.disabled = false;\n        copySigBtn.disabled = false;\n        resultPre.textContent = 'Message signed. You can now verify the signature.';\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.error(e);\n        alert('Sign operation failed: ' + e.message);\n      }\n    }\n\n    async function verifySignatureWithKey(publicKey, signatureB64, messageStr) {\n      try {\n        const sigBuf = base64ToBuf(signatureB64);\n        const data = enc.encode(messageStr);\n        const ok = await crypto.subtle.verify(\n          { name: 'ECDSA', hash: { name: 'SHA-256' } },\n          publicKey,\n          sigBuf,\n          data\n        );\n        return ok;\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.error(e);\n        throw e;\n      }\n    }\n\n    async function importPublicKeyFromPem(pem) {\n      try {\n        const b64 = unwrapPem(pem);\n        const buf = base64ToBuf(b64);\n        const key = await crypto.subtle.importKey(\n          'spki',\n          buf,\n          { name: 'ECDSA', namedCurve: 'P-256' },\n          true,\n          ['verify']\n        );\n        return key;\n      } catch (e) {\n        throw new Error('Failed to import public key: ' + e.message);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Event listeners\n    generateBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      generateBtn.disabled = true;\n      generateBtn.textContent = 'Generating…';\n      try {\n        await generateKeyPair();\n      } catch (e) {\n        alert('Key generation failed: ' + e.message);\n      } finally {\n        generateBtn.disabled = false;\n        generateBtn.textContent = 'Generate Key Pair';\n      }\n    });\n\n    exportPubBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      publicPemArea.value = exportedPublicPem;\n    });\n    exportPrivBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      privatePemArea.value = exportedPrivatePem;\n    });\n\n    copyPubBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      try {\n        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(publicPemArea.value);\n        copyPubBtn.textContent = 'Copied';\n        setTimeout(() => copyPubBtn.textContent = 'Copy', 1200);\n      } catch {\n        alert('Copy failed — try selecting and copying manually.');\n      }\n    });\n    copyPrivBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      try {\n        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(privatePemArea.value);\n        copyPrivBtn.textContent = 'Copied';\n        setTimeout(() => copyPrivBtn.textContent = 'Copy', 1200);\n      } catch {\n        alert('Copy failed — try selecting and copying manually.');\n      }\n    });\n\n    importPubBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      const pasted = prompt('Paste the public key PEM here:');\n      if (!pasted) return;\n      try {\n        const key = await importPublicKeyFromPem(pasted);\n        // Show in verifyPublicPem area for convenience\n        verifyPublicPem.value = pasted;\n        resultPre.textContent = 'Public key imported for verification.';\n      } catch (e) {\n        alert(e.message);\n      }\n    });\n\n    tamperBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      let msg = messageArea.value;\n      if (msg.length === 0) {\n        alert('Message is empty.');\n        return;\n      }\n      // Flip a character to demonstrate tampering\n      const i = Math.floor(msg.length / 2);\n      const charCode = msg.charCodeAt(i);\n      const newChar = String.fromCharCode(charCode ^ 1); // flip low bit\n      msg = msg.substring(0, i) + newChar + msg.substring(i + 1);\n      messageArea.value = msg;\n    });\n\n    clearTamper.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      messageArea.value = 'The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog';\n    });\n\n    signBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      signBtn.disabled = true;\n      signBtn.textContent = 'Signing…';\n      try {\n        await signMessage();\n      } catch (e) {\n        alert('Sign failed: ' + e.message);\n      } finally {\n        signBtn.disabled = false;\n        signBtn.textContent = 'Sign Message';\n      }\n    });\n\n    signAgain.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      signAgain.disabled = true;\n      signAgain.textContent = 'Signing…';\n      try {\n        await signMessage();\n      } catch (e) {\n        alert('Sign failed: ' + e.message);\n      } finally {\n        signAgain.disabled = false;\n        signAgain.textContent = 'Sign Again (new signature)';\n      }\n    });\n\n    copySigBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      try {\n        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(signatureArea.value);\n        copySigBtn.textContent = 'Copied';\n        setTimeout(() => copySigBtn.textContent = 'Copy Signature', 1200);\n      } catch {\n        alert('Copy failed — try selecting and copying manually.');\n      }\n    });\n\n    verifyBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      resultPre.textContent = 'Verifying…';\n      verifyBtn.disabled = true;\n      try {\n        const sigB64 = verifySignature.value.trim() || lastSignatureB64;\n        if (!sigB64) {\n          alert('No signature available. Sign a message first or paste a signature.');\n          resultPre.textContent = 'No signature.';\n          return;\n        }\n        const messageStr = messageArea.value;\n        let pubKeyToUse = null;\n        const pem = verifyPublicPem.value.trim();\n        if (pem) {\n          try {\n            pubKeyToUse = await importPublicKeyFromPem(pem);\n          } catch (e) {\n            alert(e.message);\n            resultPre.textContent = 'Failed to import public key.';\n            return;\n          }\n        } else if (cryptoKeyPair && cryptoKeyPair.publicKey) {\n          pubKeyToUse = cryptoKeyPair.publicKey;\n        } else {\n          alert('No public key available. Generate or paste a public key PEM.');\n          resultPre.textContent = 'No public key.';\n          return;\n        }\n\n        const ok = await verifySignatureWithKey(pubKeyToUse, sigB64, messageStr);\n        if (ok) {\n          resultPre.innerHTML = '<span class=\"ok\">Valid signature ✔️</span>\\nThe signature matches the message using the provided public key.';\n        } else {\n          resultPre.innerHTML = '<span class=\"bad\">Invalid signature ✖️</span>\\nThe signature does NOT match the message (message or signature may have been tampered).';\n        }\n      } catch (e) {\n        resultPre.textContent = 'Verification failed: ' + e.message;\n      } finally {\n        verifyBtn.disabled = false;\n      }\n    });\n\n    verifyTampered.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n      // Tamper the message and attempt verify to show failure\n      resultPre.textContent = 'Tampering message and verifying…';\n      verifyTampered.disabled = true;\n      try {\n        // Save original\n        const orig = messageArea.value;\n        // Tamper\n        let msg = orig || '';\n        if (msg.length === 0) msg = 'tampered';\n        const i = Math.floor(msg.length / 3);\n        const charCode = msg.charCodeAt(i) || 65;\n        const newChar = String.fromCharCode(charCode ^ 2);\n        msg = msg.substring(0, i) + newChar + msg.substring(i + 1);\n        messageArea.value = msg;\n        // Try verify\n        const sigB64 = verifySignature.value.trim() || lastSignatureB64;\n        if (!sigB64) {\n          alert('No signature available. Sign a message first.');\n          resultPre.textContent = 'No signature.';\n          return;\n        }\n        let pubKeyToUse = null;\n        const pem = verifyPublicPem.value.trim();\n        if (pem) {\n          pubKeyToUse = await importPublicKeyFromPem(pem);\n        } else if (cryptoKeyPair && cryptoKeyPair.publicKey) {\n          pubKeyToUse = cryptoKeyPair.publicKey;\n        } else {\n          alert('No public key available. Generate or paste a public key PEM.');\n          resultPre.textContent = 'No public key.';\n          return;\n        }\n        const ok = await verifySignatureWithKey(pubKeyToUse, sigB64, msg);\n        if (ok) {\n          resultPre.innerHTML = '<span class=\"ok\">Unexpectedly valid</span> — this should not happen unless the signature or keys are mismatched.';\n        } else {\n          resultPre.innerHTML = '<span class=\"bad\">Invalid signature ✖️</span>\\nAs expected, tampering the message causes verification to fail.';\n        }\n      } catch (e) {\n        resultPre.textContent = 'Verification failed: ' + e.message;\n      } finally {\n        verifyTampered.disabled = false;\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Debug/help: pre-populate verifyPublicPem with generated pub on generate\n    // (done automatically above)\n\n    // Small UX: if user pastes a PEM into verifyPublicPem, enable verify button\n    verifyPublicPem.addEventListener('input', () => {\n      // nothing special for now\n    });\n    verifySignature.addEventListener('input', () => {\n      // nothing special\n    });\n\n    // Optionally, import a public key by reading from the public PEM textarea if user double clicks\n    publicPemArea.addEventListener('dblclick', () => {\n      verifyPublicPem.value = publicPemArea.value;\n      resultPre.textContent = 'Public key copied into verification area (double-clicked).';\n    });\n\n    // Initialize\n    resultPre.textContent = 'Ready. Generate a key pair to begin.';\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
